Hey - I've found 3 issues, and left some high level feedback:

- RollbackCircuitBreakerState now takes a long list of loosely related primitive parameters (including the new ref flag); consider introducing a small state struct or context object to group these values and make the call sites and method contract easier to reason about.
- registeredForCleanup is only reset when fleetEntryName != null; if the invariant is that a null name implies no registration, it would help to either enforce that with an early return/assert or document the assumption so future changes donÔÇÖt accidentally reintroduce double-cleanup paths for the null case.

