This test only verifies that a local `if (fleetEntryName != null)` is skipped, rather than the actual rollback behavior. Please add a test that calls `RollbackCircuitBreakerState` with `fleetEntryName == null` and `registeredForCleanup == true`, asserting that (1) no dictionary entries are removed and (2) `registeredForCleanup` remains unchanged. This will exercise the real rollback path for this edge case.

Suggested implementation:

